# Environment Variables Template for Netlify

Copy these to your Netlify dashboard under Site settings â†’ Environment variables.
Replace placeholder values with your actual values.

## ===== REQUIRED VARIABLES =====

# Backend API URL
# IMPORTANT: Update this with your actual Render backend URL after deployment
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend.onrender.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL_PROD=https://your-backend.onrender.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL_DEV=http://localhost:5000

# Environment
NODE_ENV=production

## ===== HOW TO SET IN NETLIFY =====

# Method 1: Netlify Dashboard (Recommended)
# 1. Go to Site settings
# 2. Click "Environment variables" in sidebar
# 3. Click "Add a variable"
# 4. Enter key and value
# 5. Select scope: "All scopes" or specific deploy contexts
# 6. Click "Create variable"

# Method 2: Netlify CLI
# netlify env:set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL "https://your-backend.onrender.com"
# netlify env:set NODE_ENV "production"

# Method 3: netlify.toml (Not recommended for sensitive data)
# Already configured in netlify.toml with comments

## ===== IMPORTANT NOTES =====

# 1. All client-side variables MUST start with NEXT_PUBLIC_
# 2. Never expose sensitive secrets in NEXT_PUBLIC_ variables
# 3. Redeploy after adding/changing environment variables
# 4. Variables are available during build time and runtime
# 5. Different values can be set for different deploy contexts:
#    - Production (main branch)
#    - Deploy Previews (pull requests)
#    - Branch deploys

## ===== DEPLOY CONTEXTS =====

# You can set different values for different contexts:

# Production (main branch)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.myapp.com

# Deploy Previews (pull requests)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://staging-api.myapp.com

# Branch Deploys (specific branches)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://dev-api.myapp.com

## ===== OPTIONAL VARIABLES =====

# If you need to override specific settings:
# NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://myapp.com

## ===== VERIFICATION =====

# After setting variables, verify they're available:
# 1. Trigger a new deploy
# 2. Check deploy logs for environment variables
# 3. In browser console, check: console.log(process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL)
